LOL DANO!  And TJ, you sit right where I do in the big tin cans...so when they crash and break in half right in front of the wing I can run out thru the big new hole.  Have fun out there.

Yup.. were in Vancouver all right...  what a nice place... cool ocean air, super nice people...  but wow.. if you though booze was expensive in Ontario... uhhg....  you should see it here...  today were going along the coast for a Mothers day Picnic, and then tomorrow we start the serious sight seeing.. aquarium, stanley park and museums...  my cousin has a 37 foot sailboat that we will be taking a "jaunt" on that.. were having a blast.  Ill keep up the reports for you guys..  Yesterday we did a little shopping at a local market and Dug into some sushi... Jaden enjoyed hers!!
Want a nice view of the whole city TJ...take a trip up to the top of Grouse Mountain on the gondola..just North of the city.
Its on our "list"
It's not cheap...but I think it's worth the view.
LOL TJ do they make your booze out of gasoline?
If you want a really special dinner while you are out there, you have to try "The salmon House on the Hill" Fantastic food and a beautiful view.
Good idea, its even more fun to climb/hike up though.
Judging from the photo, I'd say that 18 Molson Canadian costs exactly $38.00 where you are now. Am I right??>  You'd better not stay out there too long TJ.

Just got back, saw some old growth.. that wasnt my beard....    and went out on a "island"  saw a seal and had a great day... my feet are tired... everything is hilly here... here is some more pics from today...  what a beautiful place this is...
